HEADWORD: Thrasonical
<hw>Thra*son"ic*al</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[From
<ets>Thrso</ets>, the name of a braggart soldier in Terence's
⟦ldquo⟧Eunuch:⟦rdquo⟧ cf. L. <ets>Thrasonianus</ets>.]</ety> <def>Of or
pertaining to Thraso; like, or becoming to, Thraso; bragging; boastful;
vainglorious.</def> -- <wordforms><wf>Thra*son"ic*al*ly</wf>,
<pos>adv.</pos></wordforms>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Caesar's <qex>thrasonical</qex> brag of 'I came, saw, and
overcame.'</q> <rj><qau>Shak.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

